01:01:34,393 --> 01:01:35,435
(GASPS)

754
01:01:39,606 --> 01:01:41,191
(GROANS)

755
01:01:41,275 --> 01:01:42,568
Where'd the tree go?

756
01:01:43,360 --> 01:01:45,445
-Ahh!
-Ahnh|!

757
01:01:47,948 --> 01:01:49,616
They're growing! We did it!

758
01:01:49,700 --> 01:01:50,701
We did It!

759
01:01:50,784 --> 01:01:52,119
(LAUGHING)

760
01:01:54,496 --> 01:01:57,332
SATSUKI: | thought it was a dream!
MEI: But it wasn't!

761
01:01:57,416 --> 01:02:01,795
BOTH: | thought it was a dream!
We did it!

762
01:02:17,644 --> 01:02:21,315
Mr. Kusakabe? Telegram!

763
01:02:21,398 --> 01:02:22,816
Vir. Kusakabe?

764
01:02:24,735 --> 01:02:27,070
A telegram for you.

765
01:02:27,154 --> 01:02:29,948
Huh. No one's home.

766
01:02:33,994 --> 01:02:35,912
(TRAMPLING)

767
01:02:35,996 --> 01:02:37,664
MEI: Granny!

768
01:02:42,336 --> 01:02:43,754
I'm over here.

769
01:02:45,672 --> 01:02:47,966
This one's ready to eat.

770
01:02:48,342 --> 01:02:50,927
(GRUNTING)

771
01:02:51,887 --> 01:02:53,347
(SNAP)

772
01:02:56,850 --> 01:02:58,602
What about this one, Granny?

773
01:02:58,685 --> 01:02:59,686
Try it.

774
01:02:59,770 --> 01:03:01,480
(GRUNTING)

775
01:03:01,563 --> 01:03:02,606
(SNAP)

776
01:03:06,109 --> 01:03:09,488
Wow, Granny. Your garden
is just like a market.

777
01:03:09,571 --> 01:03:13,075
We've picked enough,
haven't we? Let's take a rest.

778
01:03:19,206 --> 01:03:21,458
Mmm. Nice and cold.

779
01:03:21,541 --> 01:03:24,169
Mark, get set, go!

780
01:03:32,386 --> 01:03:33,762
It's delicious.

781
01:03:33,845 --> 01:03:36,807
I'm glad you like it.
They're very good for you.

782
01:03:36,890 --> 01:03:40,060
They've soaked up lots
of vitamins and sunshine.

783
01:03:40,560 --> 01:03:43,730
-Would they help Mom get better?
-Of course they would.

784
01:03:43,814 --> 01:03:47,651
lf your mom eats my vegetables,
| bet she'd get well right away.

785
01:03:47,734 --> 01:03:50,654
That's great, Granny.
Mom's coming home on Saturday.

786
01:03:50,737 --> 01:03:52,989
she's going to sleep with me in my bed.

787
01:03:53,073 --> 01:03:57,285
Oh, good! She's finally
leaving the hospital, is she?

788
01:03:57,369 --> 01:04:01,498
No. The doctor wants her to get used to
the new house a little at a time.

789
01:04:01,581 --> 01:04:04,000
-She goes back on Monday.
-ls that so?

790
01:04:04,084 --> 01:04:07,087
We'll feed her lots of
my vegetables while she's here.

791
01:04:07,170 --> 01:04:10,924
I'll give her the corn that | picked.
That will make her better.

792
01:04:11,007 --> 01:04:14,261
-| bet that will do her wonders.
-Yep.

793
01:04:22,102 --> 01:04:24,354
Here. The postman
left us your telegram.

794
01:04:24,438 --> 01:04:25,605
A telegram?

795
01:04:29,609 --> 01:04:32,571
What should | do with it?
Dad wont be home till evening.

796
01:04:32,654 --> 01:04:35,157
Better open it. Might be an emergency.

797
01:04:35,782 --> 01:04:37,826
VMimm-hmm.

798
01:04:39,077 --> 01:04:43,039
“Please contact Shichikokuyama."

799
01:04:43,123 --> 01:04:46,585
shichikokuyama!
It's from Mom's hospital!

800
01:04:46,668 --> 01:04:48,962
something must have happened to her.

801
01:04:50,338 --> 01:04:52,883
We have to get to the hospital
right away, Granny.

802
01:04:52,966 --> 01:04:56,636
Okay. Calm down. First, we need to get
in touch with your father.

803
01:04:56,720 --> 01:05:00,223
| Know his phone number at the
university, but we don't have a phone.

804
01:05:00,307 --> 01:05:04,311
Kanta, take Satsuki to your uncle's
house and let her use the phone.

805
01:05:04,394 --> 01:05:05,604
VMimm-hmm.

806
01:05:09,941 --> 01:05:13,153
Mei, you need to stay here with me!

807
01:05:21,703 --> 01:05:24,456
Mei, go back and stay with Granny!

808
01:05:32,798 --> 01:05:34,382
Uh!

809
01:06:01,409 --> 01:06:04,830
Hello? I'd like to place
a long-distance call, please.

810
01:06:04,913 --> 01:06:08,625
It's to my dad at Tokyo 31-13-82.

811
01:06:08,708 --> 01:06:09,709
Right.

812
01:06:11,127 --> 01:06:14,256
Now, that’s a nice girl, eh, Kanta?

813
01:06:15,465 --> 01:06:16,550
(RINGS)

814
01:06:16,633 --> 01:06:17,801
Hello?

815
01:06:17,884 --> 01:06:19,344
Yes.

816
01:06:20,136 --> 01:06:23,139
Hello? | need to speak to my dad
in the archaeology department.

817
01:06:23,223 --> 01:06:25,809
| mean, | need to speak
to Mr. Kusakabe.

818
01:06:25,892 --> 01:06:27,853
My name is Satsuki Kusakabe.

819
01:06:31,815 --> 01:06:33,984
Hello, Dad? Is that you? It's Satsuki.

820
01:06:34,067 --> 01:06:36,111
-What's wrong?
-We got <i>a</i> <i>telegram.</i>

821
01:06:36,194 --> 01:06:38,572
You're <i>to</i> <i>call</i> <i>Mom's</i> <i>doctor</i> <i>at</i> <i>the</i>
<i>hospital.</i>

822
01:06:38,655 --> 01:06:40,532
What? The hospital?

823
01:06:40,615 --> 01:06:42,826
<i>Okay.</i> I'll <i>call</i> <i>them</i> <i>right</i> <i>away.</i>

824
01:06:42,909 --> 01:06:45,662
Did something happen to her?
Do you think she's okay?

825
01:06:45,745 --> 01:06:47,414
<i>Let's</i> <i>not</i> <i>worry.</i>

826
01:06:47,497 --> 01:06:50,750
ll <i>call</i> <i>the</i> <i>hospital,</i> <i>and</i>
<i>I'll</i> <i>call</i> <i>you</i> <i>right</i> <i>back.</i> <i>Okay?</i>

827
01:06:50,834 --> 01:06:52,460
-Yeah.
<i>-Wait</i> <i>by</i> <i>the</i> <i>phone.</i>

828
01:06:52,544 --> 01:06:55,297
-Mimm-hmm.
-| need to hang up now. Okay?

829
01:06:57,632 --> 01:07:01,595
Excuse me, is it okay if | wait here?
My dad's going to call me back.

830
01:07:01,678 --> 01:07:04,347
Of course. Make yourself at home.

831
01:07:11,313 --> 01:07:13,857
Satsuki!

832
01:07:13,940 --> 01:07:15,150
(PANTING)

833
01:07:17,569 --> 01:07:22,115
(BLEATING)

834
01:07:22,198 --> 01:07:24,409
Back off! Don't touch my corn!

835
01:07:24,492 --> 01:07:25,785
It's for my mommy!

836
01:07:25,869 --> 01:07:26,912
(BLEATING)

837
01:07:26,995 --> 01:07:30,582
Too bad! She needs it
to make her better.

838
01:07:31,374 --> 01:07:32,751
(BLEATING)

839
01:07:46,306 --> 01:07:49,434
Mei, the doctor said
that Mom's not doing well.

840
01:07:49,517 --> 01:07:51,895
So she doesn't get
to come home this weekend.

841
01:07:51,978 --> 01:07:55,273
No fair!

842
01:07:55,357 --> 01:07:56,733
lt can't be helped, Mei.

843
01:07:56,816 --> 01:07:58,944
What if she came
and it made her worse?

844
01:07:59,027 --> 01:08:00,987
It's not fair!

845
01:08:02,155 --> 01:08:04,366
Mei, we just have to wait a little longer.

846
01:08:04,449 --> 01:08:08,662
-No!
-You want her to die, Mei?

847
01:08:08,745 --> 01:08:11,915
-Is that what you want?
-No!

848
01:08:11,998 --> 01:08:14,709
You're such a baby! Just grow up!

849
01:08:19,798 --> 01:08:22,550
(SNIFFLING)

850
01:08:25,679 --> 01:08:26,805
Come on, Mel.

851
01:08:27,514 --> 01:08:30,100
(CRYING)

852
01:08:30,183 --> 01:08:33,687
She's so mean!

853
01:08:34,187 --> 01:08:37,148
(CRYING)

854
01:09:00,505 --> 01:09:03,925
Come on, girls.
Let's put the laundry away.

855
01:09:04,551 --> 01:09:08,138
Oh, don't be sad. Granny's here to help.

856
01:09:15,770 --> 01:09:19,691
Don't worry. Your father is
going to stop by the hospital.

857
01:09:20,734 --> 01:09:23,820
The doctors say your mom
just has a cold.

858
01:09:23,903 --> 01:09:27,449
she should be home next Saturday.

859
01:09:31,536 --> 01:09:33,329
This is just like last time.

860
01:09:33,413 --> 01:09:37,542
They said Mom just had a little cold,
she'd be home in a few days.

861
01:09:39,252 --> 01:09:41,629
Granny, what will we do if she dies?

862
01:09:41,713 --> 01:09:43,673
Satsuki!

863
01:09:43,923 --> 01:09:46,134
Maybe she's dead already.

864
01:09:46,217 --> 01:09:49,512
(CRYING)

865
01:09:49,971 --> 01:09:52,766
Now, don't say that, sweetheart.

866
01:09:53,308 --> 01:09:57,645
How could she ever leave
such sweet girls like you?

867
01:09:57,729 --> 01:10:00,065
Oh, don't cry.

868
01:10:00,148 --> 01:10:02,358
Don't cry. It’s all right.

869
01:10:02,442 --> 01:10:05,987
I'll stay here until your father
comes home. Okay? Okay?

870
01:10:48,363 --> 01:10:50,824
Viel!

871
01:10:55,745 --> 01:10:57,163
Viel!

872
01:11:00,500 --> 01:11:02,001
Viel!

873
01:11:05,380 --> 01:11:07,507
-Did she come back?
-No.

874
01:11:07,590 --> 01:11:10,760
-She wasn't at the bus stop?
-No.

875
01:11:10,844 --> 01:11:11,928
Let's think.

876
01:11:12,011 --> 01:11:14,180
Do you know where else
she might have gone?

877
01:11:14,264 --> 01:11:18,059
| yelled at her this morning.
She wanted Mom to come home.

878
01:11:18,143 --> 01:11:21,187
Granny, | bet she went to see Mom
at the hospital!

879
01:11:21,271 --> 01:11:23,523
You think she'd try
to walk to the hospital?

880
01:11:23,606 --> 01:11:26,693
Why, that’s a three-hour walk
even for grown-ups.

881
01:11:26,776 --> 01:11:27,777
I'll go look.

882
01:11:30,029 --> 01:11:33,449
Kanta! Hurry! Run on home
and get your father!

883
01:11:33,533 --> 01:11:36,411
Mei's disappeared, and we need
all the help we can get!

884
01:11:45,503 --> 01:11:48,464
| shouldn't have yelled at her.
This is all my fault.

885
01:11:55,930 --> 01:11:58,641
Viel!

886
01:12:05,064 --> 01:12:07,817
Excuse me, mister! Hello!

887
01:12:07,901 --> 01:12:10,737
-Yeah?
-I'm looking for my sister.

888
01:12:10,820 --> 01:12:13,656
Did you happen to see
a little girl pass this way?

889
01:12:13,740 --> 01:12:16,451
Let's see. Uh, a little girl?

890
01:12:16,534 --> 01:12:20,205
Mmm, | don't think so.
| would have noticed.

891
01:12:20,288 --> 01:12:21,748
'll try the other road.

892
01:12:40,934 --> 01:12:43,436
MAN: Are you sure that this
is the way she came?

893
01:12:43,519 --> 01:12:45,063
| don't Know.

894
01:12:53,279 --> 01:12:55,949
Viel!

895
01:12:56,866 --> 01:12:59,410
(HEAVY BREATHING)

896
01:13:03,790 --> 01:13:06,125
(PANTING)

897
01:13:12,131 --> 01:13:13,841
(CAR APPROACHING)

898
01:13:16,928 --> 01:13:19,597
Stop! Please, stop!

899
01:13:21,349 --> 01:13:23,851
-Oh! Are you crazy?
-I'm looking for my little sister.

900
01:13:23,935 --> 01:13:26,646
Have you seen a girl walking this way?

901
01:13:26,729 --> 01:13:27,730
Is she lost?

902
01:13:27,814 --> 01:13:31,859
| think she's trying to walk to the
hospital. She's only four years old.

903
01:13:31,943 --> 01:13:34,404
Oh. | didn't see her. Did you?

904
01:13:34,487 --> 01:13:36,739
No. We just came from the hospital,

905
01:13:36,823 --> 01:13:40,410
and there was no sign of
a little girl on the road.

906
01:13:40,493 --> 01:13:42,787
Okay. Thanks.

907
01:13:42,870 --> 01:13:45,581
-Wait. Where'd you say you're from?
-From Matsugo.

908
01:13:45,665 --> 01:13:47,208
Matsugo! Ho!

909
01:13:47,292 --> 01:13:50,253
A four-year-old couldn't walk this far.

910
01:13:50,336 --> 01:13:51,337
(ENGINE STARTS)

911
01:13:51,421 --> 01:13:53,298
MAN: Good luck. | hope you find her.

912
01:14:03,516 --> 01:14:05,059
Satsuki!

913
01:14:06,644 --> 01:14:09,022
Kanta!

914
01:14:09,647 --> 01:14:10,606
-Find her?
-No.

915
01:14:10,690 --> 01:14:12,984
-| guess you didn't, either.
-VUimm-mmm.

916
01:14:13,067 --> 01:14:15,528
My dad's got a bunch of
people looking for her.

917
01:14:15,611 --> 01:14:17,905
| could ride my bike
to the hospital for you.

918
01:14:17,989 --> 01:14:20,366
-You should go back home.
-Check all around.

919
01:14:20,450 --> 01:14:23,745
I'm sure that Mei got lost
on her way to the hospital.

920
01:14:23,828 --> 01:14:26,622
A little while ago,
they found a sandal in the pond.

921
01:14:30,418 --> 01:14:32,378
(GASPS)

922
01:14:33,796 --> 01:14:36,716
They don't know for sure
it's Mel's sandal!

923
01:14:47,518 --> 01:14:49,854
(BREATHING HARD)

924
01:14:53,566 --> 01:14:55,234
Did you find her yet?

925
01:15:19,300 --> 01:15:20,843
MAN: We'll check the irrigation ditch.

926
01:15:20,927 --> 01:15:24,263
(PEOPLE CHATTERING)

927
01:15:24,972 --> 01:15:26,849
MAN: On the far end.

928
01:15:26,933 --> 01:15:31,104
(CHANTING)

929
01:15:31,479 --> 01:15:34,607
It's much deeper over there.
You should try there first!

930
01:15:34,690 --> 01:15:36,192
MAN: Are there more poles?

931
01:15:44,617 --> 01:15:45,618
(CHANTING)

932
01:15:45,701 --> 01:15:46,702
(CLAMORING)

933
01:15:46,786 --> 01:15:47,870
Huh?

934
01:15:49,414 --> 01:15:51,290
WOMAN: It's Satsuki.

935
01:15:54,460 --> 01:15:56,546
Here. Is this Mel's?

936
01:16:05,888 --> 01:16:08,766
-It's not hers.
-On!

937
01:16:08,850 --> 01:16:10,768
(SIGHS)

938
01:16:13,020 --> 01:16:14,480
Onh...

939
01:16:14,564 --> 01:16:15,690
(SIGHS)

940
01:16:17,400 --> 01:16:19,193
Oh, thank goodness.

941
01:16:19,277 --> 01:16:22,989
| was positively certain
that sandal belonged to Mei.

942
01:16:23,072 --> 01:16:25,158
All right. Granny just got carried away.

943
01:16:25,241 --> 01:16:27,910
Hey! It's not her sandal!

944
01:16:33,374 --> 01:16:36,127
Everyone, | know you've spent
a lot of time here,

945
01:16:36,210 --> 01:16:38,171
but we still need your help.

946
01:16:48,055 --> 01:16:49,724
Satsuki!

947
01:17:04,906 --> 01:17:06,032
Please.

948
01:17:06,115 --> 01:17:08,326
(PANTING)

949
01:17:08,409 --> 01:17:10,786
Let me in to see Totoro. Mel's lost.

950
01:17:10,870 --> 01:17:13,372
Its getting dark,
and she's out there all alone.

951
01:17:13,456 --> 01:17:15,917
Please let me in to see him.
It's an emergency.

952
01:17:20,963 --> 01:17:23,090
(BREATHING HARD)

953
01:17:39,607 --> 01:17:40,650
(THUDDING)

954
01:17:40,733 --> 01:17:41,734
(SCREAMING)

955
01:17:41,817 --> 01:17:45,321
(THUDDING)

956
01:17:45,404 --> 01:17:46,572
(GASPS)

957
01:17:46,656 --> 01:17:47,740
Totoro!

958
01:17:49,951 --> 01:17:54,163
Totoro, Mei's lost. | looked everywhere
for her, but | couldn't find her.

959
01:17:54,247 --> 01:17:56,999
Please help me. | have to find her.

960
01:17:57,792 --> 01:18:01,003
I'm sure she's scared
half to death by now.

961
01:18:01,087 --> 01:18:03,005
| don't Know where else to turn.

962
01:18:03,089 --> 01:18:05,883
(SOBBING)

963
01:18:21,274 --> 01:18:23,276
(ROARING)

964
01:18:39,208 --> 01:18:42,628
(INHALES DEEPLY)

965
01:18:42,712 --> 01:18:45,548
(ROARING)

966
01:18:53,598 --> 01:18:56,559
(YOWLING)

967
01:19:02,398 --> 01:19:04,191
No one else can see it, can they?

968
01:19:34,180 --> 01:19:35,389
Huh?

969
01:19:51,572 --> 01:19:53,032
FOREST-SWAMP

970
01:19:53,115 --> 01:19:56,535
CEMETERY-SHRINE

971
01:19:56,619 --> 01:19:57,620
MEI

972
01:19:57,703 --> 01:20:01,248
-Mei.
-Viel!

973
01:20:12,843 --> 01:20:14,970
(LAUGHING)

974
01:20:16,555 --> 01:20:17,765
GRANNY: Mel!

975
01:20:17,848 --> 01:20:18,808
(GASP)

976
01:20:18,891 --> 01:20:19,892
Viel!

977
01:20:27,525 --> 01:20:29,151
The trees are parting!

978
01:20:37,993 --> 01:20:39,370
(BARKING)

979
01:20:59,098 --> 01:21:01,142
(SIGHS)

980
01:21:01,225 --> 01:21:03,102
SATSUKI: Mel!

981
01:21:06,439 --> 01:21:10,192
Satsuki!

982
01:21:10,276 --> 01:21:13,404
-Where are you?
-Viel!

983
01:21:23,622 --> 01:21:26,459
-Me!!
-SatsukIi!

984
01:21:28,335 --> 01:21:31,797
-Oh! You're okay.
-I'm sorry.

985
01:21:34,300 --> 01:21:37,219
Were you trying to take your
corn to Mom at the hospital?

986
01:21:37,303 --> 01:21:38,721
VMimm-hmm.

987
01:21:38,804 --> 01:21:42,933
(YOWLING)

988
01:21:45,561 --> 01:21:48,063
HOSPITAL

989
01:21:49,815 --> 01:21:52,276
You're going to take us to the hospital?

990
01:21:54,487 --> 01:21:55,571
Thank you!

991
01:21:55,654 --> 01:21:57,573
(LAUGHING)

992
01:22:04,580 --> 01:22:07,875
I'm sorry. | don't know why
the hospital sent a telegram.

993
01:22:07,958 --> 01:22:09,752
It's just a cold.

994
01:22:09,835 --> 01:22:14,882
| hope it didn't upset them too much.
I've caused enough grief already.

995
01:22:14,965 --> 01:22:17,468
When they see you're all right,
they'll be fine.

996
01:22:17,551 --> 01:22:20,429
Weill just wait a little
longer for a weekend together.

997
01:22:20,513 --> 01:22:23,974
Don't worry. We've made it this far.

998
01:22:24,058 --> 01:22:27,353
The girls act so strong, but | think
it's harder than they let on.

999
01:22:27,436 --> 01:22:28,604
Especially Satsuki.

1000
01:22:28,687 --> 01:22:33,400
-She tries to act so adult.
